get.description:
Returns all draft evaluations for a workflow, organized by draft.

**Frontend Integration:**
-   Use `draft_ids_ordered` to iterate through drafts in version order (v1, v2, v3, ...)
-   Use `drafts[draft_id]` for O(1) lookup of specific drafts
-   `latest_grade` provides quick access to the most recent grade
-   `evaluation_count` shows how many times each draft was evaluated
-   `all_evaluations` array contains the complete history in chronological order
-   The last element of `all_evaluations` is always the most recent evaluation
-   `is_selected` indicates which draft is the current default for operations

**Example Usage:**
```javascript
// Iterate drafts in order
response.draft_ids_ordered.forEach(id => {
  const draft = response.drafts[id];
  console.log(`v${draft.version}: Grade ${draft.latest_grade}`);
});

// Get specific draft
const draft_v2 = response.drafts["relationtool-abc_v2"];

// Get latest evaluation
const latest = draft_v2.all_evaluations[draft_v2.all_evaluations.length - 1];

// Get selected draft
const selected = response.drafts[response.selected_draft_id];
```
